 and relationships. Ramona Bullik portrays nine longitudinal case studies in a mixed-methods design with narrative analysis granting insight into the developments and stabilities in the interviews. The focus on religious married couples allows to carve out the role of faith and the changing view on the spouse and the joint life. The portraits of three non-religious women show how meaning is made outside the frame of organized religion. Individual survey data are put into relation with a larger sample, answering the claim for idiothetic research.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 4aBielefeld University Press. 4aCouples. 4aDevelopment. 4aLife. 4aLiterature. 4aLongitudinal Research. 4aMixed Methods. 4aNarrative Identity. 4aPhilosophical Anthropology. 4aPsychology of Religion. 4aQualitative Analysis. 4aReligion. 4aReligious Studies. 4aSociology of Religion. 7aRELIGION / General.2bisacsh  aBielefeld University Press.  aCouples.  aDevelopment.  aLife.  aLiterature.  aLongitudinal Research.  aMixed Methods.  aNarrative Identity.  aPhilosophical Anthropology.  aPsychology of Religion.  aQualitative Analysis.  aReligion.  aReligious Studies.  aSociology of Religion.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Complete eBook Package 2023z9783111024950oZDB-23-TGP08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Complete eBook Package 2024z9783111332376oZDB-23-TGP40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839471227zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839471227zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839471227/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA  aZDB-23-TGPb2023